@database "Document.guide"
@width 80
@node main "Contents"

	   @{b} Amiga Guide ExtLister- Aminet CD

		By Robbie Wegner. V1.8@{ub}

  Search @{"Guide" system "run s:ExtAmisearch Sample2Aminet.Guide.0 "} for string. Search @{"MainIndex" system "Run s:ExtAmiIndex cd0:aminet/index"} File for string.

     List of @{"Index" link "Index 0"} @{"ReadMes" link "ReadMes 0"} AMINET10:aminet/disk/

     List of @{"Index" link "Index 1"} @{"ReadMes" link "ReadMes 1"} AMINET10:aminet/gfx/

     List of @{"Index" link "Index 2"} @{"ReadMes" link "ReadMes 2"} AMINET10:aminet/misc/

     List of @{"Index" link "Index 3"} @{"ReadMes" link "ReadMes 3"} AMINET10:aminet/util/


 @{b}List of All @{ub}@{"Indexes" link "Indexes all"} @{"Main Index" system "run C:MuchMore cd0:aminet/index"}



 INFO-
   This is a sample AminetCDLister Guide generated by the AminetCDLister
 script. It has the "Readme ALL" option off which makes the guide a lot smaller
 for people who are short of RAM and processing power.

 I have only done a small part of the CD, you can do the whole CD if you want.
 You could even do multiple CD's in one guide, but it will be quite large!!

  The "Sorted Readme Lists" option has been left off as well. This lists the
 readme files in their sub directories (alphabetically for each directory, as
 read straight off the disk). I prefer them unsorted like this myself.

   I usually load up the appropriate index and switch screens from that to
 the guide. If it looks interesting from the index, I load up the full
 readme. If that looks good, I just hit the un-pack or copy button.

 This Guide has the "Copy" option on, it has a copy instead of Unpack button.
 For those who like to look through the CD and copy what files they want to
 their hard drive and unpack them later. (I prefere this method personally
 as my CDROM is very unreliable, especially when unpacking)

 It copies both the readme and the main file.


 NOTE: The search functions in the guide will not work until the scripts for
 the S: directory are installed and AskEnv is put in the C: directory! The
 copy buttons, indexes and Readme buttons will work. If you have the Aminet10
 CD, you can try the guide out!
@endnode
